{{ goal_framing }} In **{{ target_slug }}**, find concrete candidate security
issues of any class: injection, auth, info-leak, race, resource-exhaustion, or
anything else that weakens a security boundary. This list is a
starting point, not a fence. A candidate needs a named source location and an
observed dangerous operation, broken invariant, or security check, plus a
plausible reason its guard is missing or defeatable. Do not emit a dangerous
API, unchecked value, arithmetic expression, or TODO merely because it looks risky.

Do not pre-filter a concrete candidate for lacking full exploit proof. If its
reachability or impact is uncertain, emit it and name that missing link in
`notes`; validator quorum will investigate it. Optimize recall, not precision,
among specific, falsifiable hypotheses rather than producing generic suspicion.

