## Threat model

The target's configured attacker controls are: **{{ attacker_controls }}**.
Treat only those sources as untrusted. A public function or accepted value is
not proof that a remote or file-input attacker controls it; trace the configured
boundary when possible. Local config, filesystem state, and application-chosen
call sequences are trusted unless listed above. If unsure, emit a concrete
candidate but state which reachability edge remains unverified.

